The paper deals with strategic communication in network settings, which involves different objectives for the encoder and the decoder. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. The paper also studies the compression and communication problems with the receiver and/or transmitter side information setting, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories.
